data.chText: （除女王或王后外的）王室女成员；（尤指）公主
data.enText: a female member of a royal family who is not a queen, especially the daughter or granddaughter of the king or queen

data.chText: 肯特郡迈克尔公爵夫人
（受宠溺而自以为优越的）娇小姐
data.enText: a young woman who has always been given everything that she wants, and who thinks that she is better than other people

data.chText: （男子对女孩或年轻女子的称呼）大小姐
data.enText: used as a form of address by a man to a girl or young woman

means: (除女王或王后外的)王室女成员
(受宠溺而自以为优越的)娇小姐

tr: a female member of a royal family other than the queen (especially the daughter of a sovereign)

value.def: A princess is a female member of a royal family, usually the daughter of a king or queen or the wife of a prince.

example.ex: Princess Anne topped the guest list.
example.tran: 安妮公主排在宾客名单之首。
摩纳哥公主卡罗琳·林登
